    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger </strong>then peel and finely slice <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>then chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks (save a few leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Chop your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> finely (deseed if you can't handle the heat!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> ground cumin </strong>and<strong> sliced shallot </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>and blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>green chilli paste</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped coconut cream </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>soy sauce </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>baking paper </strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>remaining shallot</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot batons</strong>, <strong>pepper strips </strong>and<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>shallot </strong>to the tray[s] with the <strong>remaining soy sauce, cumin seeds </strong>and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender \u2013 this is your <strong>soy-spiced veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>green chilli paste </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 2-3 min \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut & green chilli sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Gently add the <strong>fish </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook, covered, for 5 min or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-and-green-chilli-double-basa-with-soy-spiced-veg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>coconut & green chilli fish </strong>with the <strong>soy-spiced veg</strong> and <strong>basmati rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
